result.execSummary:
The defendant Brittany K Zahn was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manufacture/Deliver Heroin (<3g) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(d)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: Includes read-in amounts and defendant stipulates to restitution amount.

Outstanding financial obligations shall be paid from all prison wages at a rate of 25% and the balance due as a condition of extended supervision.  If extended supervision is revoked or will discharge with financial obligations owing, a judgment shall be entered.

Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.

Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcohol or controlled substance without a valid prescription and then take medication as prescribed.

Defendant shall have no contact, direct or indirect, with Christopher D.

Defendant shall have no contact with any drug dealers or users or be where drugs are used or sold.

Defendant shall pay any supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample.

Defendant shall cooperate with a psychological assessment and comply with recommendations.

Defendant shall cooperate with a cognitive behavioral program and comply with recommendations.

Defendant shall provide agent with list of medications and notify the agent of any change in prescription within 48 hours of the change.

Defendant shall notify any medical professional providing care of addiction history.
Defendant shall undergo an AODA assessment and comply with treatment recommendations.
Defendant shall obtain and maintain full time employment.
